&lt;div&gt;• Build partnering relationships with customers and individuals responsible for making purchasing decisions&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;• Manage multiple, ongoing opportunities focused on selling OEM and aftermarket parts &amp;amp; supplies&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;• Visit and support customer accounts daily&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;• Identify parts sales opportunities with new and existing customers&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;• Actively manages sales growth plans for assigned accounts&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;• Actively make customers aware of product offerings and promotions&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;• Attend or host sales related entertainment and&amp;nbsp;events, occasionally outside normal business hours&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;• Possess knowledge of all vendor lines, and be able to demonstrate and discuss with customers&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;The Required Profile&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;• Growth mindset,&amp;nbsp;team oriented,&amp;nbsp;and driven to win&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;• High school diploma or equivalent.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;• 2 to 5 years HVAC industry experience is required.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;• Prior experience in B2B outside sales.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;• Excellent initiative, interpersonal communications skills, and a demonstrated ability to influence others.&lt;/div&gt;
